snippet: A rare bipartisan maneuver forces a vote, now set for Oct. 26, on an issue that has become a litmus test for conservatives.
abstract: Bipartisan group of House members enacts petition forcing vote on renewing charter of Export-Import Bank, which had expired in June.
lead_paragraph: A rare bipartisan maneuver forces a vote, now set for Oct. 26, on an issue that has become a litmus test for conservatives.

headline.print_headline: Bipartisan Coalition Forces New Vote on Ex-Im Bank
headline.main: Export-Import Bank Will Come to New House Vote
